title: Half Acre Cycling's Women/Girls/Trans Road Rac
12th Annual IC3 Hillsboro-Roubaix
description:
12th Annual IC3 Hillboro-Roubaix Road Race
Saturday, March 23, 2013
course:
Wish you could race a Spring Classic in Europe?  
Race the 12th annual Hillsboro-Roubaix Spring Classic, through the brick streets and rural roads of beautiful Hillsboro, Illinois.  Just  60 miles, but a world away from St. Louis, MO, this is small town America at its best.  Racers will tour the brick streets of Hillsboro in a rolling neutral start, then race a 29 mile loop that has all you want in a Spring Classic: Flat open back roads heading into a northern headwind, rolling terrain, short but challenging climbs, twisty descents, and village streets paved in brick.  Sorry, no real pave, the bricks will have to suffice! 39/25 gearing is recommended for one stiff climb, road surfaces are good enough for 700 x 23 clinchers.  There is some gravel in corners.
registration:
Pre-Registration at BikeReg.com
$10 extra for same day registration
Online registration ends 10pm Wednesday, March 20, 2013. Refunds will be given less Bikereg.com fees. NO REFUNDS AFTER 10PM SUNDAY, MARCH 10, 2013. Licenses sold onsite Current USA Cycling Rules will be enforced. Held under a USA Cycling Event Permit.


Race Day Registration is at Hillsboro Free Methodist, 1400 Seymour Avenue, Hillsboro, IL 62049 

REGISTRATION CLOSES @ 10AM SHARP ON RACE DAY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
notes:
Race Director
Todd Harris 
ic3hillsboro@gmail.com
------ 
 
Facilities
The Hillsboro Free Methodist Church offers its Fellowship Hall for our convenience and comfort during registration and awards. Treat with respect and gratitude.

No street parking near Start/Finish!
directions:
Directions
From St. Louis
Take 40/64 East to I-55 North.  Go 50 miles to IL-16, Gillespie/Litchfield exit. 
 
From Northern Illinois
Take I-55 South to IL-16, Gillespie/Litchfield exit.
 
From I-55
Go about 10 miles EAST on IL-16 to Hillsboro. 
Turn SOUTH onto Main Street. When the road starts to bend gently to the left, stay right and turn onto West Fairground Avenue.  Continue to Seymour- turn left- and park in the parking lot of the Free Methodist Church.  
 
No street parking near Start/Finish

title: Quad Cities Criterium
description:
Who: Over 650 cyclists from across the U.S., Canada, and Europe 
What: 14 Criterium bicycle races, 8 kids races, Bike Rodeo, and food. 
When: Monday May 27, 2013 
Where: The District, Downtown Rock Island, Illinois
◦48th running of the Quad Cities Criterium
◦Fourth race in the Memorial Day Weekend series
Friday, Burlington Road Races, Burlington, IA
Saturday, Snake Alley Criterium, Burlington, IA
Sunday, Melon City Criterium, Muscatine, IA 
Monday, Quad Cities Criterium, Rock Island, IL
course: This flat, fast 3/4 mile hourglass shaped course will include a raucous cheering crowd and one of the best wheel pits in the world. There is plenty of parking and the course is just one block from the Mississippi River and Schweibert Riverfront Park. We know you will have a great time racing and celebrating in The District.
registration: This year for the first time, registration will be through USAC\'s online services ONLY as well as on-site the day of with a $10 late fee.  NO SNAIL MAIL REGISTRATIONS.  Registration closes 30 minutes before each race.
notes: See race website at www.QuadCitiesCriterium.com for a full history on this storied event.
directions:
From Chicago (I-80)
Take I-80 west, and continue on I-280 west to Illinois 92. Take the Rock Island exit and follow IL-92 to downtown.
 
From Chicago (I-88 / east west toll way)
Take I-80 east exit, and follow I-80 approximately 5 miles to I-74 west. Continue on I-280 west to Illinois 92. Take the Rock Island exit and follow IL-92 to downtown.
 
From Peoria
Take I-74 west, and continue on I-280 west to Illinois 92. Take the Rock Island exit and follow IL-92 to downtown.
 
From Iowa City
Take I-80 east to I-280 east, cross the Mississippi river, and take Illinois 92 exit and follow IL-92 to downtown.
 
From Muscatine\'s Weed Park 
For the scenic drive: 
From Weed Park take Parkington Drive west to the \"T\" at Park Ave. Turn left (south) on Park Ave to Washington St. Turn left (East) on Washington St., which then turns into Iowa Route 22. Follow Iowa Route 22 through the cities of Fairmont, Montpelier, and Buffalo to I-280 East over the Mississippi River and to Illinois 92 East, to downtown Rock Island.

For a faster drive: 
From Weed Park take Parkington Drive west to the \"T\" at Park Ave. Turn right (north) on Park Ave. Take Park Ave. to US Highway 61 north. Turn right. Take US-61 north to I-280 east, then over the Mississippi River to Illinois 92 east to downtown Rock Island.  

In downtown Rock Island, Illinois 92 becomes 1st Ave. Turn right on to 16th Street, left on 3rd Ave to the Holiday Inn Hotel for lodging and registration.
